HEADWORD: Alkarsin
<hw>Al*kar"sin</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Alkali</ets> + <ets>ars</ets>enic + <ets>-in</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A spontaneously inflammable liquid, having a
repulsive odor, and consisting of cacodyl and its oxidation products; --
called also <altname>Cadel's fuming liquid</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alka-seltzer</ent>⟦br⟧
